- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a likely category as the paper deals with games with costs and winning strategies, which are common topics in game theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses complexity and memory bounds for solving parity games with weights. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with solving games and finding winning strategies, which are relevant to AI applications. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses extensions of parity games and their properties, which could be relevant to programming language semantics.
